WEBVTT

00:07.200 --> 00:10.633
[Psychedelic pop music playing
over radio]

00:10.667 --> 00:17.467
**

00:17.500 --> 00:24.267
**

00:24.300 --> 00:26.067
[Volume increases]

00:26.100 --> 00:30.867
[Rewinding]

00:30.900 --> 00:32.367
[Brakes creak]

00:32.400 --> 00:33.733
[Engine stops]

00:33.767 --> 00:38.000
I ask you to do this,
Charlie, for me.

00:38.033 --> 00:41.533
**

00:41.567 --> 00:44.567
For love.

00:44.600 --> 00:47.333
For our great
revolution.

00:47.367 --> 00:51.433
What -- What happens
when I get there?

00:51.467 --> 00:54.900
You will drop off the car
at Salzburg train station.

00:54.933 --> 00:57.000
Place the keys in the exhaust
and walk away.

00:57.033 --> 00:58.633
And then?

00:58.667 --> 01:00.633
And then my people
will seek you out.

01:00.667 --> 01:03.967
**

01:04.000 --> 01:05.700
Show me.

01:05.733 --> 01:08.633
**

01:08.667 --> 01:09.833
I need to see it.

01:09.867 --> 01:11.000
[Ceiling rips]

01:11.033 --> 01:17.700
**

01:17.733 --> 01:19.133
[Exhales sharply]
Becker: Don't worry.

01:19.167 --> 01:22.500
It won't actually be used
to blow anyone up.

01:22.533 --> 01:27.200
Semtex is popular
because it's stable.

01:27.233 --> 01:29.133
But I wouldn't
light a cigarette in there.

01:29.167 --> 01:34.467
**

01:34.500 --> 01:39.700
**

01:39.733 --> 01:43.733
Greek Drachma,
Yugoslavian Dinar,

01:43.767 --> 01:46.467
Austrian Schilling,
Deutsche Mark.

01:46.500 --> 01:51.267
**

01:51.300 --> 01:53.133
I will take you
to the first border.

01:53.167 --> 01:54.500
That's close
as we can get.

01:54.533 --> 01:55.867
Marty said...

01:55.900 --> 01:59.367
**

01:59.400 --> 02:00.967
[Car door closes]

02:01.000 --> 02:07.867
**

02:07.900 --> 02:14.833
**

02:14.867 --> 02:21.767
**

02:22.533 --> 02:29.533
**

02:31.133 --> 02:38.133
**

02:39.733 --> 02:46.700
**

02:48.300 --> 02:55.300
**

02:56.900 --> 03:03.900
**

03:05.500 --> 03:12.500
**

03:14.100 --> 03:21.067
**

03:31.100 --> 03:34.767
Charlie: Taking me to the border
wasn't part of the plan, was it?

03:34.800 --> 03:38.833
The Yugoslav border
shouldn't prove difficult.

03:38.867 --> 03:42.833
Now, the Austrian border,
that's more serious.

03:42.867 --> 03:47.067
Stay alert.
Show them no nerves.

03:47.100 --> 03:48.333
[Paper rustles]

03:48.367 --> 03:49.967
Since you don't
keep a diary,

03:50.000 --> 03:51.767
we've decided
to keep one for you.

04:03.433 --> 04:05.333
[Gasps]

04:05.367 --> 04:07.167
[Scoffs]

04:07.200 --> 04:09.800
Wha...

04:09.833 --> 04:12.167
[Sighs]

04:12.200 --> 04:14.300
You have a habit
of chewing your pencils

04:14.333 --> 04:15.700
when you're thinking.

04:15.733 --> 04:18.533
[Inhales sharply]
This is completely normal.

04:24.667 --> 04:28.233
And we wrote to one another,
dozens of letters,

04:28.267 --> 04:31.500
arranging our meeting
in Greece.

04:31.533 --> 04:33.100
Where are they?

04:33.133 --> 04:36.000
I do not permit you
to carry them with you.

04:36.033 --> 04:37.700
Shame.

04:37.733 --> 04:39.800
Could've done
with a saucy read.

04:39.833 --> 04:43.533
You have kept them
in a safe place in your home.

04:43.567 --> 04:46.533
I asked you where might
be best to hide them.

04:46.567 --> 04:50.667
And I said inside the pocket
of the case of my first guitar.

04:50.700 --> 04:52.300
Gift from my dad.

04:52.333 --> 04:54.400
[Psychedelic pop music playing]

04:54.433 --> 04:56.500
[Pencil crunches]

04:56.533 --> 05:03.533
**

05:05.200 --> 05:12.200
**

05:13.900 --> 05:15.733
[Lighter clicks]

05:15.767 --> 05:19.333
[Woman singing in Greek
playing over radio]

05:19.367 --> 05:22.533
**

05:22.567 --> 05:25.067
[Breathes shakily]

05:25.100 --> 05:32.100
**

05:33.867 --> 05:40.867
**

05:42.567 --> 05:49.567
**

05:51.333 --> 05:58.333
**

06:00.033 --> 06:07.033
**

06:08.833 --> 06:12.100
[Chuckles]

06:12.133 --> 06:13.433
[Sighs deeply]

06:14.833 --> 06:18.433
He tricked me.
I thought I broke him.

06:18.467 --> 06:20.100
Miss Bach:
He lied about Salzburg.

06:20.133 --> 06:22.200
He could lie again.

06:22.233 --> 06:26.100
He's clever.

06:26.133 --> 06:28.367
So, what
do we do now?

06:28.400 --> 06:33.800
Kurtz:
Now...it's my turn.

06:33.833 --> 06:37.833
**

06:37.867 --> 06:42.967
[Door rattles]

06:43.000 --> 06:45.467
[Door opens]

06:45.500 --> 06:52.500
**

06:54.667 --> 06:59.833
My name is Martin Kurtz.

06:59.867 --> 07:06.867
**

07:07.167 --> 07:08.367
Hm.

07:08.400 --> 07:11.733
**

07:11.767 --> 07:14.333
[Grunts]

07:14.367 --> 07:15.533
[Sniffs]

07:15.567 --> 07:21.033
**

07:21.067 --> 07:24.567
"Kurtz"
is sounding like

07:24.600 --> 07:29.433
the word "short"
in German,

07:29.467 --> 07:31.700
as I'm sure
you know.

07:31.733 --> 07:35.633
My friends used to call me
"Short-fuse Marty."

07:35.667 --> 07:37.333
Hm.

07:41.533 --> 07:44.367
Anna Witgen traveled
to Salzburg

07:44.400 --> 07:49.100
on her way to deliver
your brother's latest bomb.

07:49.133 --> 07:53.333
Always a second plan,
never the same place twice.

07:53.367 --> 07:57.300
Isn't that your method?

07:57.333 --> 08:02.767
Maybe there is more of Khalil
in you than I thought.

08:02.800 --> 08:06.200
Your people were forced
into the wilderness,

08:06.233 --> 08:11.300
deprived of their homes,
left to suffer in the camps.

08:14.900 --> 08:17.867
Did they do this to you
in the camp in Jordan?

08:17.900 --> 08:19.267
[Michel groans]

08:19.300 --> 08:24.267
I grew up
in a camp myself

08:24.300 --> 08:27.467
a long time ago.

08:27.500 --> 08:29.367
I know how it feels.

08:29.400 --> 08:33.167
[Whimpers, groans]

08:33.200 --> 08:36.167
Then you are worse
than any of them.

08:36.200 --> 08:38.033
Mm, perhaps.

08:38.067 --> 08:39.433
But you...

08:39.467 --> 08:40.700
[Muffled groan]

08:40.733 --> 08:44.533
You are not made
for this fight...

08:44.567 --> 08:46.833
[Exhales sharply]
...Salim.

08:46.867 --> 08:49.067
[Breathes shakily]
A red Mercedes

08:49.100 --> 08:52.433
with a blonde bombshell
in the passenger's seat --

08:52.467 --> 08:53.900
fine.

08:53.933 --> 08:55.100
Not a bomb.

08:55.133 --> 08:56.967
[Grunts]

09:00.267 --> 09:07.033
Now, when I realized
you lied about the drop,

09:07.067 --> 09:11.067
that made me angry.

09:11.100 --> 09:16.800
But then I recognized something,
and I laughed.

09:16.833 --> 09:20.233
We have been lying
to you.

09:24.033 --> 09:28.400
Come here.
I have something to show you.

09:28.433 --> 09:31.800
It's okay.

09:31.833 --> 09:35.433
It's perfectly safe.

09:38.233 --> 09:39.400
[Door slamming on tape player]

09:39.433 --> 09:41.267
[Tape player clicks,
sound stops]

09:44.467 --> 09:47.667
Come.

09:47.700 --> 09:49.667
The truth.

09:54.100 --> 10:01.067
**

10:01.867 --> 10:08.867
**

10:09.667 --> 10:12.600
The photo of Khalil --

10:12.633 --> 10:16.033
It was pieced together
using pictures of your family

10:16.067 --> 10:19.800
and of you,
by the talented Mr. Schwilli.

10:19.833 --> 10:21.533
The rest of the team,
you've met.

10:21.567 --> 10:28.567
**

10:31.167 --> 10:36.367
Your receipts.
Your collection of matchbooks.

10:36.400 --> 10:39.000
We found it very helpful.

10:39.033 --> 10:44.800
**

10:44.833 --> 10:47.833
[Window blind rustles]

10:47.867 --> 10:53.733
[Children playing outside]

10:55.133 --> 10:57.233
You are in Munich.

10:57.267 --> 10:59.833
You have been here
for two days.

11:01.933 --> 11:03.933
Why?

11:03.967 --> 11:07.633
Why are you
showing me this?

11:07.667 --> 11:09.533
Life, Salim.

11:11.233 --> 11:12.400
[Playing continues]

11:12.433 --> 11:14.733
Where are you
taking that car?

11:24.800 --> 11:28.600
When I first came
to Europe,

11:28.633 --> 11:30.833
do you know what
surprised me the most?

11:33.700 --> 11:35.367
Nobody cares.

11:35.400 --> 11:40.733
**

11:40.767 --> 11:42.467
Nobody cares.

11:42.500 --> 11:47.333
**

11:47.367 --> 11:51.500
Enough bloodshed, Salim.

11:51.533 --> 11:56.300
**

11:56.333 --> 12:00.033
There, uh...

12:00.067 --> 12:04.167
There is no
location set.

12:04.200 --> 12:06.967
I decide it.

12:07.000 --> 12:10.367
**

12:10.400 --> 12:12.900
Thank you.

12:12.933 --> 12:17.133
[Whimpering]

12:17.167 --> 12:21.067
A square in Austria.
[Sniffles]

12:21.100 --> 12:24.533
It will need
good vantage points,

12:24.567 --> 12:25.733
good cover.

12:25.767 --> 12:27.100
A train ride from here

12:27.133 --> 12:29.900
so Charlie is never
alone for too long,

12:29.933 --> 12:31.600
and light tourism too.

12:31.633 --> 12:34.667
We don't want
any collateral.

12:34.700 --> 12:37.000
[Sniffling]

12:37.033 --> 12:41.533
Salim is honest now.

12:41.567 --> 12:43.033
[Rock music playing over radio]
* Harana

12:43.067 --> 12:45.200
[Imitating guitar riff]

12:45.233 --> 12:47.433
* Bi-ni-ni-na-na-na-na,
let's go *

12:47.467 --> 12:49.800
* Ah-me-na-na
and then pick your toe *

12:49.833 --> 12:52.000
* Take me to the park
and then *

12:52.033 --> 12:55.400
* Me-ne-me-ne-me is enshala

12:55.433 --> 12:56.633
* Me-ne-mon-oh-nom-oh-no

12:56.667 --> 12:58.867
* Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh

13:01.067 --> 13:05.467
Kurtz: There has been
a slight change of location.

13:05.500 --> 13:08.500
Instead of Salzburg,

13:08.533 --> 13:11.167
we wish to move
our work to...

13:11.200 --> 13:13.567
[Pen scratching]

13:13.600 --> 13:19.500
[Piano playing in distance]

13:19.533 --> 13:21.567
Alexis: Well...

13:21.600 --> 13:23.367
if you want me
to be of use to you,

13:23.400 --> 13:25.167
Herr Schulmann,

13:25.200 --> 13:27.200
I have to be of more use
to Cologne,

13:27.233 --> 13:28.433
as you promised.

13:28.467 --> 13:30.567
[Plate clinks]

13:30.600 --> 13:32.867
[Chewing]

13:32.900 --> 13:35.167
If I were you,

13:35.200 --> 13:38.033
I'd keep my eyes
on the roads

13:38.067 --> 13:43.333
of Southern Germany
in the coming week.

13:43.367 --> 13:44.933
I have a feeling

13:44.967 --> 13:48.733
a little gift might
light up your investigation

13:48.767 --> 13:51.467
sooner
than you think.

13:51.500 --> 13:52.800
Is this an operation --

13:52.833 --> 13:54.133
[Clicks tongue]

13:54.167 --> 14:00.567
Sometimes we must take
our victories, Paul,

14:00.600 --> 14:02.933
not question them.

14:02.967 --> 14:05.533
[Lighter clicks]

14:05.567 --> 14:10.100
**

14:10.133 --> 14:11.300
[Lighter clangs]

14:11.333 --> 14:13.100
Good sir.

14:13.133 --> 14:19.033
[Yugoslavian folk music
playing]

14:19.067 --> 14:20.033
[Keys rattle]

14:20.067 --> 14:21.733
Rachel: Charlie.

14:21.767 --> 14:23.133
Bloody hell,
what are you doing here?

14:23.167 --> 14:25.567
Oh, my God.
[Chuckles]

14:25.600 --> 14:29.233
What are you --
How fantastic to see you.

14:29.267 --> 14:31.767
Long way from Greece.
Yeah, long way.

14:31.800 --> 14:34.400
Wh-Where are you heading to?
Did you ever make it to Delphi?

14:34.433 --> 14:35.933
Yeah, we did.
We did, actually.

14:35.967 --> 14:37.533
[Chuckles] Yeah.
It was really nice.

14:37.567 --> 14:39.333
[Tile clinks]

14:39.367 --> 14:41.300
Have you never played
this game before?

14:41.333 --> 14:42.600
Oh, piss off.

14:42.633 --> 14:44.733
[Snickers]

14:44.767 --> 14:48.400
You still headed to Salzburg,
by the way?

14:48.433 --> 14:50.400
Heard it's deadly dull
off-season.

14:53.400 --> 14:56.600
Well, you were the one
who suggested it.

14:56.633 --> 14:58.600
Should I go
somewhere else?

14:58.633 --> 15:00.267
Kleinalm is pretty.

15:00.300 --> 15:01.667
[Tile clinks]

15:01.700 --> 15:05.267
Nice cafÃ©s,
lovely square.

15:05.300 --> 15:07.267
Gutigplatz.

15:07.300 --> 15:14.267
**

15:14.300 --> 15:20.233
You know that old man
in Greece?

15:20.267 --> 15:22.100
Did he really
have a wife?

15:22.133 --> 15:23.433
[Tile clinks]

15:23.467 --> 15:25.033
[Lighter clatters]

15:25.067 --> 15:26.833
Did she jump,
or was she pushed?

15:26.867 --> 15:33.667
**

15:33.700 --> 15:34.700
Jumped.

15:34.733 --> 15:39.233
**

15:39.267 --> 15:40.433
[Snaps fingers]

15:40.467 --> 15:42.533
-Sir?
-I need to send a telegram.

15:42.567 --> 15:46.233
**

15:46.267 --> 15:50.100
I decide it.

15:50.133 --> 15:54.467
I send a telegram to my lawyers
in Zurich, twice.

15:54.500 --> 15:56.800
Send it twice.
Once now...

15:56.833 --> 15:57.800
[Coins rattle]

15:57.833 --> 15:59.600
...once in the morning.

15:59.633 --> 16:00.833
Litvak: After rush hour,

16:00.867 --> 16:03.333
traffic drops down
to its minimum.

16:03.367 --> 16:05.867
That's our golden hour.

16:05.900 --> 16:08.600
Litvak:
So far so good.

16:08.633 --> 16:10.067
It isn't bad.

16:10.100 --> 16:11.633
It's nothing till
she delivers the ca--

16:11.667 --> 16:13.400
Gadi says
she will deliver.

16:13.433 --> 16:18.033
And if Gadi says so,
I believe him.

16:18.067 --> 16:22.300
Okay.

16:22.333 --> 16:24.167
But, of course,
you're right.

16:24.200 --> 16:26.200
The drop-off
is the thing.

16:27.900 --> 16:31.300
Kurtz: You have enough people
for Gutigplatz.

16:31.333 --> 16:34.500
This is your moment,
Shimon.

16:34.533 --> 16:37.300
You tell me what you need,
you shall have it.

16:37.333 --> 16:41.367
**

16:41.400 --> 16:44.433
[Truck roars]

16:44.467 --> 16:50.067
[Rain falling]

16:50.100 --> 16:52.700
Charlie:
Shit, shit, shit.

16:59.567 --> 17:03.367
[Brakes creak]

17:06.000 --> 17:07.233
[Snores]

17:07.267 --> 17:09.700
[Rain echoing on roof]

17:17.233 --> 17:18.400
[Sighs]

17:18.433 --> 17:20.333
[Engine revs]

17:20.367 --> 17:27.333
**

17:27.367 --> 17:31.700
[Man shouting shouting in German
in distance]

17:31.733 --> 17:33.800
[Breathes shakily]

17:33.833 --> 17:35.000
[Lighter clicks]

17:35.033 --> 17:37.700
[Puffing]
[Lighter clicks]

17:37.733 --> 17:38.933
[Blows]

17:38.967 --> 17:43.333
**

17:43.367 --> 17:47.900
I -- I-I've quit.

17:47.933 --> 17:51.567
[Speaking German]

17:51.600 --> 17:55.400
Do you speak English?
Sorry.

17:55.433 --> 17:57.400
Step out
of the vehicle.

17:57.433 --> 17:59.500
License
and passport.

17:59.533 --> 18:00.500
Right.

18:00.533 --> 18:02.900
[Shouting in German continues]

18:02.933 --> 18:09.900
**

18:11.333 --> 18:13.900
[Truck engine revs]

18:13.933 --> 18:20.500
**

18:20.533 --> 18:21.700
[Truck brakes hiss]

18:21.733 --> 18:24.500
**

18:24.533 --> 18:27.867
Shit.

18:27.900 --> 18:29.067
[Lighter clicks]

18:29.100 --> 18:31.533
**

18:31.567 --> 18:35.467
I thought
you gave up.

18:35.500 --> 18:36.767
[Scoffs]

18:36.800 --> 18:39.700
I'm a -- I'm a terrible
quitter.

18:39.733 --> 18:41.100
Awful.
[Chuckles nervously]

18:41.133 --> 18:43.367
You are nervous.

18:43.400 --> 18:46.233
[Car door closes]

18:46.267 --> 18:47.333
N--

18:47.367 --> 18:50.700
**

18:50.733 --> 18:52.667
Oh. Uh...

18:52.700 --> 18:54.633
**

18:54.667 --> 18:56.500
[Trunk clanks]

18:56.533 --> 18:58.033
[Gasps]

18:58.067 --> 18:59.867
**

18:59.900 --> 19:02.900
This is very serious,
madam.

19:02.933 --> 19:08.833
This amount, it -- it will kill
all of us, not just you.

19:08.867 --> 19:10.867
Smuggling moonshine
is doubly illegal.

19:10.900 --> 19:12.733
[Crate clatters]

19:12.767 --> 19:15.000
We keep this here.

19:15.033 --> 19:16.800
Just this once.

19:16.833 --> 19:17.900
Sorry.

19:17.933 --> 19:19.833
[Keys rattle]

19:19.867 --> 19:26.867
**

19:29.633 --> 19:33.200
[Teleprinter clacking]

19:33.233 --> 19:37.300
**

19:37.333 --> 19:39.000
She's made the cross.

19:39.033 --> 19:43.767
**

19:43.800 --> 19:45.900
[Charlie exhales]

19:45.933 --> 19:49.667
Litvak: It can't be
much longer now.

19:49.700 --> 19:54.967
[Charlie breathing heavily]

19:55.000 --> 19:58.433
Yes, she's here.

19:58.467 --> 20:02.567
**

20:02.600 --> 20:04.367
[Brakes creak]

20:04.400 --> 20:06.433
**

20:06.467 --> 20:08.600
[Over radio] This is it.
Focus now.

20:08.633 --> 20:12.033
[Exhales sharply]

20:12.067 --> 20:13.633
Hm.

20:13.667 --> 20:20.067
**

20:20.100 --> 20:26.533
**

20:26.567 --> 20:27.733
[Keys rattle]

20:27.767 --> 20:28.933
[Car door opens]

20:28.967 --> 20:30.533
[Inhales deeply]

20:30.567 --> 20:33.867
**

20:33.900 --> 20:35.333
[Car door closes]

20:35.367 --> 20:41.333
**

20:41.367 --> 20:47.400
**

20:47.433 --> 20:49.333
Oh.

20:49.367 --> 20:51.100
**

20:51.133 --> 20:55.233
[Keys rattle]

20:55.267 --> 20:56.500
[Sighs]

20:56.533 --> 20:58.100
[Trunk closes]

20:58.133 --> 21:01.233
Litvak: Well done, Charlie.
Now just walk away.

21:01.267 --> 21:08.267
**

21:21.633 --> 21:24.600
**

21:24.633 --> 21:28.200
[Indistinct conversations
in German in distance]

21:28.233 --> 21:35.233
**

21:36.633 --> 21:43.600
**

21:45.000 --> 21:46.733
[Sighs]
One slivovitz, please.

21:46.767 --> 21:48.567
Ein slivovitz.

21:48.600 --> 21:54.133
**

21:54.167 --> 21:59.733
**

22:03.133 --> 22:04.167
[Woman speaking German]

22:04.200 --> 22:07.433
Um, sorry,
I -- uh...

22:07.467 --> 22:10.100
I d-- I don't have
any Austrian money.

22:10.133 --> 22:11.967
I-I only have pounds.

22:12.000 --> 22:17.033
[Woman speaking German]

22:17.067 --> 22:18.333
[Speaking German]

22:18.367 --> 22:19.633
Ah.

22:19.667 --> 22:23.100
[Coins rattle]

22:23.133 --> 22:25.267
-Danke.
-Okay.

22:31.100 --> 22:32.833
Thank you, Father.

22:37.133 --> 22:38.300
[Gulps]
Ahh.

22:38.333 --> 22:39.633
[Glass thuds]

22:46.433 --> 22:50.233
Ah. That could've
really have blown up.

22:50.267 --> 22:52.400
Litvak: [Over radio]
She's on the move.

22:52.433 --> 22:54.300
Train station, please.

22:54.333 --> 22:55.900
[Over radio] She's asked
for the train station.

22:55.933 --> 22:58.667
**

22:58.700 --> 23:01.900
[Car door closes, engine starts]

23:01.933 --> 23:08.933
**

23:11.500 --> 23:15.167
Litvak: Where the hell
are you going?

23:15.200 --> 23:18.000
[Over radio]
You'll be fine.

23:18.033 --> 23:19.500
Focus on the car only.

23:19.533 --> 23:21.033
I'm staying
with Charlie.

23:21.067 --> 23:22.900
[Over radio]
No, that wasn't the plan.

23:22.933 --> 23:25.167
[Over radio]
She'll need me.

23:25.200 --> 23:27.567
-But Marty said...
-Shimon.

23:27.600 --> 23:29.833
Marty said I was in charge
of this operation.

23:29.867 --> 23:30.967
-Shimon.
-What?

23:31.000 --> 23:32.000
[Feedback]

23:32.033 --> 23:34.400
He's turned
his radio off.

23:34.433 --> 23:35.833
Great.

23:35.867 --> 23:38.500
Now we wait.

23:40.967 --> 23:44.033
[Footsteps echoing
on cobblestones]

23:44.067 --> 23:46.500
[Chewing]

23:49.567 --> 23:54.867
[Motorcycle engine revs]

23:54.900 --> 23:56.967
Shimon.
Check this out.

23:57.000 --> 23:58.033
[Tires screech]

23:58.067 --> 23:59.833
Look.

23:59.867 --> 24:03.033
**

24:03.067 --> 24:04.333
Rachel:
[Over radio] Contact.

24:04.367 --> 24:06.033
Rose: [Over radio]
Too fast, surely?

24:06.067 --> 24:08.167
Flash bastard could get
picked up by the police.

24:08.200 --> 24:09.333
Litvak: [Over radio]
Sit tight, please.

24:09.367 --> 24:11.767
[Tires screech]

24:11.800 --> 24:18.767
**

24:24.133 --> 24:26.100
[Over radio]
That's Anna Witgen.

24:26.133 --> 24:28.033
The rider will be
keeping watch.

24:28.067 --> 24:31.300
Hold position until she gets
the key out of the exhaust.

24:31.333 --> 24:34.700
**

24:34.733 --> 24:36.300
[Keys rattle]

24:36.333 --> 24:37.800
They have another key.

24:37.833 --> 24:40.100
Two telegrams, two keys,
of course.

24:40.133 --> 24:42.000
Keep your eyes on the car.

24:42.033 --> 24:43.800
**

24:43.833 --> 24:45.767
[Car door shuts]

24:45.800 --> 24:48.267
Shit.

24:48.300 --> 24:50.067
That's Rossino.

24:50.100 --> 24:51.400
Daniel: Who?

24:51.433 --> 24:54.400
A petty little
left-wing journalist.

24:54.433 --> 24:56.400
We've been sniffing him out
since Milan,

24:56.433 --> 24:57.600
but we can never prove
a connection

24:57.633 --> 25:00.600
to Khalil's network.

25:00.633 --> 25:02.200
That just changed.

25:02.233 --> 25:05.667
Welcome to the fight,
Mr. Rossino.

25:05.700 --> 25:07.533
[Engine starts, keys rattle]

25:07.567 --> 25:09.667
[Engine revs]

25:09.700 --> 25:14.667
**

25:14.700 --> 25:19.633
**

25:19.667 --> 25:21.633
[Motorcycle engine revs]

25:21.667 --> 25:23.300
**

25:23.333 --> 25:24.567
[Over radio]
Should we split up?

25:24.600 --> 25:26.033
They've gone
in opposite directions.

25:26.067 --> 25:28.233
Focus on the car only.

25:28.267 --> 25:29.967
Shall I follow him
at least?

25:30.000 --> 25:33.900
We can't just
let him go.

25:33.933 --> 25:35.833
No, we need everyone
on that car.

25:35.867 --> 25:41.300
**

25:41.333 --> 25:46.833
**

25:46.867 --> 25:48.033
[Gear cranks]

25:48.067 --> 25:49.700
[Engine revs]

25:49.733 --> 25:52.300
Litvak: [Over radio] Easy, easy.
Don't scare her off.

25:52.333 --> 25:57.400
**

25:57.433 --> 25:58.600
Rachel: [Over radio]
She's slowing down.

25:58.633 --> 26:04.400
**

26:04.433 --> 26:06.400
She's pulling over
to the side of the road.

26:06.433 --> 26:08.467
Keep going.
Keep going.

26:08.500 --> 26:10.267
[Engine revs]

26:10.300 --> 26:13.433
**

26:13.467 --> 26:15.233
[Brakes creak]

26:15.267 --> 26:18.033
[Engine idling]

26:18.067 --> 26:19.867
[Engine revs]

26:19.900 --> 26:26.767
**

26:26.800 --> 26:29.467
[Over radio]
She's checking the cargo.

26:29.500 --> 26:34.967
**

26:35.000 --> 26:36.300
Turn your car around.

26:36.333 --> 26:38.300
We'll get her as soon
as she's called this in.

26:38.333 --> 26:42.900
**

26:42.933 --> 26:45.367
[Receiver clicks]

26:45.400 --> 26:47.367
[Coin rattles]

26:47.400 --> 26:51.700
**

26:54.400 --> 26:55.800
Let's move.
Let's move.

26:55.833 --> 26:57.433
[Engine revs]

26:57.467 --> 26:58.733
[Tires screech]

26:58.767 --> 27:00.533
[Engine revs]

27:00.567 --> 27:01.933
[Tires screech]

27:01.967 --> 27:08.667
**

27:08.700 --> 27:10.800
-Aah! Nein!
-Don't let her go!

27:10.833 --> 27:12.933
[Anna shouting indistinctly]

27:12.967 --> 27:15.467
-Don't get up!
-Grab her legs good!

27:15.500 --> 27:18.133
[Anna screams]
Litvak: Hold her!
Hold her!

27:18.167 --> 27:20.233
-Grab her legs! Grab her legs!
-Watch out! Watch out!

27:20.267 --> 27:24.533
[Anna screaming]

27:24.567 --> 27:25.733
[Anna sobs]

27:25.767 --> 27:30.100
[Men shouting indistinctly]

27:30.133 --> 27:31.500
[Anna straining]

27:31.533 --> 27:34.233
I can't hold her.
[Shouting indistinctly]

27:34.267 --> 27:35.800
Catch her!
Catch her!

27:35.833 --> 27:37.733
[Rose shouting indistinctly]

27:37.767 --> 27:38.800
Okay,
get the syringe!

27:38.833 --> 27:41.533
[Anna screaming]

27:41.567 --> 27:46.133
[All shouting indistinctly]

27:46.167 --> 27:47.500
[Screams]

27:47.533 --> 27:49.967
Do it! Do it!
Do it!

27:50.000 --> 27:54.500
[Screaming]

27:54.533 --> 27:55.500
Aah!

27:55.533 --> 27:58.167
[Panting]

27:58.200 --> 28:00.333
Rose: Come on.
Come on.

28:00.367 --> 28:03.867
**

28:03.900 --> 28:05.000
[Car door shuts]

28:05.033 --> 28:06.000
-Go!
-Go! Go!

28:06.033 --> 28:11.200
[Bells tolling in distance]

28:11.233 --> 28:13.267
[Flinches]

28:13.300 --> 28:14.767
[Bottles clink]

28:14.800 --> 28:20.600
[Teleprinter clacking]
[Breathing heavily]

28:20.633 --> 28:22.600
[Clock ticking]

28:22.633 --> 28:27.067
[Tolling continues]

28:27.100 --> 28:28.733
[Door closes]

28:32.767 --> 28:35.667
I did all right,
didn't I?

28:35.700 --> 28:37.333
Marty says
you're a star.

28:37.367 --> 28:38.700
[Chuckles]
[Bottle clinks]

28:38.733 --> 28:40.967
He wants to thank you
in person tomorrow.

28:44.367 --> 28:48.233
And what about you?

28:48.267 --> 28:50.900
Do you want
to thank me in person?

28:50.933 --> 28:53.400
[Ticking continues]

29:03.467 --> 29:06.633
You did a good thing
today.

29:06.667 --> 29:10.867
I enjoyed it.

29:10.900 --> 29:14.200
I loved it.

29:14.233 --> 29:18.333
Is that what happens?
It gets addictive?

29:18.367 --> 29:20.700
If you're the type.

29:20.733 --> 29:22.267
Are you?

29:28.767 --> 29:32.900
Why did you tell me
about the explosives...

29:32.933 --> 29:34.700
when I got in the car?

29:38.667 --> 29:40.900
One question
at a time.

29:40.933 --> 29:42.733
Hmm.

29:48.900 --> 29:53.900
Because...

29:53.933 --> 29:56.967
you are the type.

29:57.000 --> 29:58.967
You said you would
try to lie to me

29:59.000 --> 30:01.000
as little as possible.

30:09.800 --> 30:11.900
You wanted me to say no,
didn't you?

30:16.967 --> 30:20.000
Is it wrong, Gadi?

30:20.033 --> 30:21.500
What we're doing?

30:25.500 --> 30:28.267
Or were you trying to help me
for another reason?

30:32.100 --> 30:35.667
You should run a bath.

30:35.700 --> 30:39.033
You need to relax.

30:39.067 --> 30:41.733
All right.

30:41.767 --> 30:44.533
But don't fall asleep
whilst I'm in it,

30:44.567 --> 30:47.433
because I'm going
to drink myself stupid.

30:54.133 --> 30:58.133
[Receiver clatters,
rotary phone dials]

30:58.167 --> 31:02.300
[Indistinct conversations
in distance]

31:02.333 --> 31:04.733
[Water trickling]

31:08.167 --> 31:11.567
Charlie:
I heard room service.

31:11.600 --> 31:12.833
Make me a drink?

31:16.000 --> 31:18.767
After tonight, you don't know
when you'll see me again.

31:20.200 --> 31:21.500
[Bottles clink]

31:21.533 --> 31:23.467
You're going home.

31:23.500 --> 31:26.133
Leaves the audience
wanting more.

31:26.167 --> 31:29.400
Uncertainty
is the way we live.

31:29.433 --> 31:32.000
[Ice clinks]
Every night together
can be our last.

31:32.033 --> 31:34.100
Then we better
make the most of it.

31:38.533 --> 31:41.667
Your drink's ready.

31:41.700 --> 31:43.200
[Spoon stirs]

31:43.233 --> 31:44.167
Charlie?

31:44.200 --> 31:47.067
[Spoon clanks]

31:47.100 --> 31:48.333
[Door opens]

31:54.100 --> 31:56.467
[Breathing softly]

31:56.500 --> 32:02.933
**

32:02.967 --> 32:04.567
Mm.

32:04.600 --> 32:11.600
**

32:11.933 --> 32:13.100
[Light switch clicks]

32:13.133 --> 32:18.833
**

32:18.867 --> 32:20.633
[Bottles clank]

32:20.667 --> 32:23.467
**

32:23.500 --> 32:25.867
[Fork and knife scraping]

32:25.900 --> 32:31.133
**

32:31.167 --> 32:34.500
[Bag rustles]

32:34.533 --> 32:35.600
[Dish clanks]

32:35.633 --> 32:39.800
[Coffee pours]

32:39.833 --> 32:41.833
[Pitcher clanks]

32:41.867 --> 32:48.667
**

32:48.700 --> 32:50.033
[Ring clatters]

32:50.067 --> 32:53.433
**

32:53.467 --> 32:54.633
[Watch clatters]

32:54.667 --> 32:57.100
**

32:57.133 --> 33:00.200
[Pendant rattles]

33:00.233 --> 33:02.000
[Pendant clatters]

33:02.033 --> 33:08.867
**

33:08.900 --> 33:15.767
**

33:15.800 --> 33:18.200
Our best, best girl.

33:18.233 --> 33:20.767
Hm.

33:20.800 --> 33:26.467
Now, from now on,
we won't be writing the play.

33:26.500 --> 33:29.767
Now the play has to come
to you in England.

33:29.800 --> 33:31.967
Oh, I'm booked in a job.
"As -- As You Like It."

33:32.000 --> 33:33.367
Then before you go,

33:33.400 --> 33:36.167
there is someone
we think you should meet.

33:36.200 --> 33:38.767
In a way, you are already
well acquainted.

33:51.000 --> 33:52.367
[Charlie breathes heavily]

33:54.700 --> 33:56.400
[Tape player clicks]

33:56.433 --> 33:58.967
Michel: When I was 11,

33:59.000 --> 34:01.533
I crouched
in a homemade shelter

34:01.567 --> 34:06.600
while the Jordanians
poured rockets into our camp.

34:06.633 --> 34:08.367
[Tape player clicks]

34:08.400 --> 34:10.133
Michel.

34:12.133 --> 34:14.900
What did you do to him?

34:14.933 --> 34:17.733
He was sedated.
That's all.

34:19.967 --> 34:23.333
We haven't touched a hair
on his pretty head.

34:26.933 --> 34:30.533
Come on, Charlie.
This is important for your role.

34:39.967 --> 34:41.300
What's in that thing?

34:41.333 --> 34:42.933
Kurtz: Never mind.

34:46.033 --> 34:47.367
[Screaming]

34:47.400 --> 34:49.500
[Handcuffs rattling]

34:58.167 --> 34:59.300
No!

34:59.333 --> 35:01.733
[Screams]

35:01.767 --> 35:04.867
[Straining]

35:04.900 --> 35:11.900
**

35:12.767 --> 35:19.100
Daniel: Birth mark,
scar, scar, scars.

35:19.133 --> 35:20.133
[Door opens]

35:20.167 --> 35:25.733
**

35:25.767 --> 35:31.300
**

35:31.333 --> 35:33.867
So the fiction
becomes truth.

35:33.900 --> 35:38.867
**

35:38.900 --> 35:43.867
**

35:43.900 --> 35:45.933
Go on.

35:47.700 --> 35:50.300
Kurtz: They'll question you,
Charlie.

35:50.333 --> 35:53.667
You need to know
every inch.

35:53.700 --> 35:56.900
**

35:56.933 --> 35:58.400
That's enough.

35:58.433 --> 36:01.400
**

36:01.433 --> 36:03.600
I said that's enough.

36:03.633 --> 36:05.733
Now put some clothes
on him.

36:05.767 --> 36:10.833
**

36:10.867 --> 36:16.000
**

36:16.033 --> 36:18.233
What did you expect?

36:18.267 --> 36:20.233
I know that was difficult,
Charlie.

36:20.267 --> 36:21.667
It's cruel.

36:21.700 --> 36:23.300
You should save your sympathy
for the innocent.

36:23.333 --> 36:26.100
-He's a child.
-He killed a child.

36:26.133 --> 36:28.633
**

36:28.667 --> 36:30.767
Your British government
promised Palestine

36:30.800 --> 36:33.467
to the Arabs
and to the Jews.

36:33.500 --> 36:34.767
That's when
all this started.

36:34.800 --> 36:37.367
What's that
got to do with me?

36:37.400 --> 36:38.967
Being naive
doesn't absolve you.

36:39.000 --> 36:41.700
Yes, it does!
Yes, it does!

36:41.733 --> 36:44.067
You can't have it
both ways.

36:44.100 --> 36:47.633
Victim one day,
tyrant the next.

36:47.667 --> 36:50.467
An actress one day,
a moralist the next?

36:50.500 --> 36:55.767
**

36:55.800 --> 36:59.600
How do you live
with it, Gadi?

36:59.633 --> 37:00.800
The guilt.

37:00.833 --> 37:05.067
**

37:05.100 --> 37:07.933
What -- Where are you
taking me?

37:07.967 --> 37:14.967
**

37:16.367 --> 37:23.367
**

37:24.667 --> 37:28.033
We remember.

37:30.267 --> 37:32.033
Never call me
"Gadi" again.

37:34.267 --> 37:36.933
[Dogs barking in distance]

37:45.667 --> 37:49.333
[Bells tolling in distance]

37:51.533 --> 37:54.100
These are photocopies

37:54.133 --> 37:57.000
of his letters to you.

37:57.033 --> 37:59.833
You kept the originals
in your flat.

38:10.000 --> 38:11.567
Mine to him?

38:11.600 --> 38:13.300
Yes.

38:17.100 --> 38:18.500
Bit desperate.

38:22.133 --> 38:24.500
Charlie the romancer.

38:27.333 --> 38:29.100
Charlie the penitent.

38:32.700 --> 38:36.467
Charlie
the hard-nosed bitch.

38:36.500 --> 38:39.767
Thank you, Jose.

38:39.800 --> 38:41.633
If you could just lend me
that gun of yours,

38:41.667 --> 38:45.333
and I'll just pop outside
and shoot myself.

38:45.367 --> 38:47.567
You're in love.

38:49.667 --> 38:54.567
You need to write these out
in your own handwriting.

38:54.600 --> 38:56.700
Let the thoughts
become yours.

38:58.967 --> 39:01.267
You really think
they'll come for me?

39:03.267 --> 39:05.733
Yes.

39:05.767 --> 39:07.900
What about Michel?

39:10.233 --> 39:11.600
If you hold him in there
for too long,

39:11.633 --> 39:14.733
they'll know
something's up.

39:14.767 --> 39:16.900
Won't they?

39:16.933 --> 39:21.833
You need to let him go,
or at least put him on trial.

39:25.233 --> 39:27.267
He'll be accounted for.

39:30.033 --> 39:31.667
Each letter
a different pen.

39:49.733 --> 39:50.900
[Pen scratching]

39:50.933 --> 39:56.367
"I am waiting.
Hungry."

39:56.400 --> 39:59.000
**

39:59.033 --> 40:03.433
"I am alone without you.

40:03.467 --> 40:08.767
This grey city is a tomb.

40:08.800 --> 40:13.967
I can't sleep,
can't eat."

40:14.000 --> 40:17.533
**

40:17.567 --> 40:22.733
"Thoughts of your body
burn inside me."

40:22.767 --> 40:24.767
**

40:24.800 --> 40:27.133
[Sighs] God.

40:27.167 --> 40:34.167
**

40:35.233 --> 40:42.233
**

40:43.367 --> 40:45.733
"I want you
to tear me apart

40:45.767 --> 40:50.100
to piece me
back together.

40:50.133 --> 40:55.167
Make me a new face,
a new body.

40:55.200 --> 40:57.500
Make me another soul.

40:57.533 --> 41:00.700
As you said,

41:00.733 --> 41:04.533
our bodies and bloods
will be mixed.

41:04.567 --> 41:06.567
This thought is all
that can sustain me

41:06.600 --> 41:10.533
through these hollow nights
of yearning,

41:10.567 --> 41:13.400
the balm to the ache
of your absence."

41:13.433 --> 41:20.433
**

41:22.600 --> 41:25.933
My love, I would have it
that we would be --"

41:25.967 --> 41:32.933
**

41:35.300 --> 41:38.733
[Breathing heavily]

41:38.767 --> 41:42.800
**

41:42.833 --> 41:45.667
Charlie, Charlie.
Charlie.

41:45.700 --> 41:52.700
**

41:53.200 --> 41:56.833
Charlie...

41:56.867 --> 42:02.833
**

42:02.867 --> 42:08.833
**

42:08.867 --> 42:10.100
[Gasps]

42:10.133 --> 42:17.133
**

42:18.267 --> 42:21.833
Our bodies and bloods
will be mixed.

42:21.867 --> 42:23.867
[Gasps]

42:23.900 --> 42:25.067
[Table rattles]

42:25.100 --> 42:26.833
[Breathing heavily]

42:26.867 --> 42:31.333
**

42:31.367 --> 42:32.700
[Sniffles]

42:32.733 --> 42:36.633
**

42:36.667 --> 42:39.900
You're going home,
Charlie.

42:39.933 --> 42:40.900
Tomorrow.

42:40.933 --> 42:43.467
[Sobbing]

42:43.500 --> 42:47.200
[Sniffles]

42:47.233 --> 42:49.267
That's where
they'll come for you.

42:49.300 --> 42:50.867
What?

42:50.900 --> 42:57.900
**

42:58.033 --> 43:05.000
**

43:05.200 --> 43:06.967
[Wind blowing]

43:07.000 --> 43:09.800
[Vehicle approaches]

43:12.433 --> 43:14.300
[Brakes creak]

43:17.533 --> 43:19.067
[Keys rattle]

43:20.733 --> 43:22.000
The psychopath
admits --

43:22.033 --> 43:23.000
[Door opens]

43:23.033 --> 43:25.067
Hi, Gadi.

43:25.100 --> 43:27.867
[Door closes]
The psychopath admits
Bad Godesberg.

43:27.900 --> 43:30.967
She half-admits Zurich.

43:31.000 --> 43:32.767
Has she given
any names?

43:32.800 --> 43:33.967
Her own.

43:34.000 --> 43:36.433
She refuses to give
a first name.

43:36.467 --> 43:37.933
Makes no sense.

43:37.967 --> 43:42.333
Michel took her
on a few trips in his car,

43:42.367 --> 43:45.233
taught her how to shoot a gun
in some woods,

43:45.267 --> 43:46.533
and a few other details

43:46.567 --> 43:48.467
that can help us
with the fiction.

43:48.500 --> 43:50.267
Miss Bach
is working on it now.

43:50.300 --> 43:52.167
No knowledge
of Khalil?

43:52.200 --> 43:53.800
She's insane, Marty.

43:53.833 --> 43:55.767
Hurt her, she acts like
she enjoys it.

43:55.800 --> 43:57.200
Stop hurting her,
she regains the strength

43:57.233 --> 43:58.833
and gives us nothing.

43:58.867 --> 44:01.567
So we hurt girls, too,
these days, huh?

44:01.600 --> 44:04.533
You're the expert.

44:04.567 --> 44:06.767
Should I make her
fall in love with me, Gadi?

44:06.800 --> 44:08.767
So she doesn't notice
the pain?

44:08.800 --> 44:12.033
Shh.
Does it play, Gadi?

44:14.033 --> 44:15.900
Yeah, it plays.

44:15.933 --> 44:17.600
Rossino delivers it
to the square,

44:17.633 --> 44:19.800
where she picks up
the Mercedes from Charlie.

44:19.833 --> 44:21.500
It's all true.

44:21.533 --> 44:23.333
Then she drives it
towards Munich,

44:23.367 --> 44:26.233
meets Michel on the way.

44:26.267 --> 44:29.333
Untrue, but we're
the only people who know that.

44:29.367 --> 44:32.333
So, right now they're
screwing each other senseless

44:32.367 --> 44:36.500
somewhere in the countryside,
lost to the world.

44:36.533 --> 44:38.333
Lost to the world.

44:40.633 --> 44:43.700
Well, that will
also be true.

44:47.233 --> 44:50.800
**

44:50.833 --> 44:52.467
[Door closes]

44:52.500 --> 44:56.200
[Keys rattle]

44:56.233 --> 44:57.667
[Keys clatter]

44:57.700 --> 45:03.067
**

45:03.100 --> 45:08.467
**

45:08.500 --> 45:11.733
[Engine revs]

45:11.767 --> 45:13.867
[Bag rustles]

45:13.900 --> 45:20.867
**

45:22.200 --> 45:29.200
**

45:30.500 --> 45:32.267
[Rubber band snaps]

45:32.300 --> 45:36.167
**

45:36.200 --> 45:37.467
[Rattle]

45:37.500 --> 45:41.700
**

45:41.733 --> 45:44.267
Michel:
"My hometown, Al-Khalil.

45:44.300 --> 45:46.467
The Jews call it Hebron."

45:46.500 --> 45:48.900
Hebron is one
of the only places

45:48.933 --> 45:52.333
from which
the Jews were never exiled.

45:52.367 --> 45:56.800
It is therefore possible that
Jewish blood flows in my veins,

45:56.833 --> 46:00.200
yet I am not ashamed.

46:00.233 --> 46:05.833
"Did I tell you that
my father admired the Jews?"
[Receiver rattles]

46:05.867 --> 46:09.267
"He believed we should
make a common society..."
[Receiver dings]

46:11.133 --> 46:13.000
...wanted to summon
the neighbouring Jews

46:13.033 --> 46:14.800
to our village,

46:14.833 --> 46:16.700
to speak with them.

46:16.733 --> 46:18.700
[Pen clanks]

46:18.733 --> 46:22.400
The Zionists will tell you
that we had no culture.

46:22.433 --> 46:24.267
They will say
we lived in mud huts

46:24.300 --> 46:28.633
and went about
in stinking rags.

46:28.667 --> 46:31.100
But we are a decent people.

46:31.133 --> 46:33.967
[Indistinct conversations]
"Can you believe me, Charlie?"

46:34.000 --> 46:38.900
[Footsteps,
doors opening, closing]

46:38.933 --> 46:41.900
Charlie, I told you.

46:41.933 --> 46:43.467
I know.

46:43.500 --> 46:46.000
I know.
You're closing early.

46:46.033 --> 46:47.500
I mean...

46:52.500 --> 46:53.767
[Glass clanks]
[Coughs]

46:53.800 --> 46:56.200
Can you keep
the ladies' lights on?

46:56.233 --> 46:58.733
Don't want me pissing
on the floor.

46:58.767 --> 47:01.167
[Vehicles driving in distance]

47:06.600 --> 47:07.667
[Mug clinks]

47:07.700 --> 47:10.067
There's coffee.

47:10.100 --> 47:11.567
[Slurps]

47:12.900 --> 47:13.933
[Mug clinks]

47:13.967 --> 47:15.600
Of a kind.

47:19.967 --> 47:21.733
[Mug clanks]

47:21.767 --> 47:23.567
[Sighs softly]

47:26.200 --> 47:28.133
Damn it!

47:28.167 --> 47:32.967
Stop staring at me,
Gadi!

47:33.000 --> 47:34.833
Am I that pretty?

47:34.867 --> 47:37.333
[Vehicles driving]

47:44.800 --> 47:47.133
Do we have
to go this far?

47:47.167 --> 47:51.767
There's no other way.

47:51.800 --> 47:53.567
I know.

47:53.600 --> 47:54.900
I know, but --

47:54.933 --> 47:56.533
There's no other way.

48:01.200 --> 48:03.367
Marty said so.

48:03.400 --> 48:07.700
[Cars echoing on bridge]

48:10.300 --> 48:13.567
You can see
another option, huh?

48:13.600 --> 48:17.500
Are you sure you've considered
every possible option?

48:17.533 --> 48:19.467
Made every possible
promise?

48:19.500 --> 48:21.533
No innocents!

48:21.567 --> 48:24.933
That is what
I promised you, Gadi.

48:24.967 --> 48:27.500
No innocent people.

48:27.533 --> 48:28.533
I misheard.

48:28.567 --> 48:30.533
Yes, you misheard.

48:30.567 --> 48:31.967
Like always.

48:32.000 --> 48:35.100
We have another player
confirmed -- Rossino.

48:35.133 --> 48:38.033
That is another step closer
to Khalil.

48:38.067 --> 48:42.033
Charlie is in place.
What can you not see here?!

48:42.067 --> 48:44.167
The surgeon.

48:49.500 --> 48:52.067
The girl is exposed.

48:52.100 --> 48:56.033
[Water running]

48:56.067 --> 48:58.267
[Water stops]

49:03.467 --> 49:05.167
[Stall door bangs]

49:09.167 --> 49:11.200
[Stall door bangs]

49:11.233 --> 49:12.800
[Breathing heavily]

49:12.833 --> 49:15.267
[Inhales deeply]

49:15.300 --> 49:19.200
[Sighs sharply]

49:19.233 --> 49:24.000
[Exhaling shakily]

49:24.033 --> 49:26.200
[Breathing heavily]

49:26.233 --> 49:27.600
[Doorknob rattles]

49:27.633 --> 49:29.000
[Light switch clicks]

49:29.033 --> 49:31.000
[Tarp rustles]

49:31.033 --> 49:34.700
**

49:34.733 --> 49:36.700
[Car door opens]

49:36.733 --> 49:42.033
**

49:42.067 --> 49:47.367
**

49:47.400 --> 49:52.067
I asked each boy and girl
personally

49:52.100 --> 49:57.033
if they wanted
to stand down.

49:57.067 --> 50:00.367
They all begged me
to go through with it.

50:00.400 --> 50:03.833
[Insects chirping]

50:03.867 --> 50:07.567
You remember
at the Munich Olympics?

50:07.600 --> 50:12.767
When the German police
voted among themselves to...

50:12.800 --> 50:16.467
when they chose to abandon
their rescue operation...

50:16.500 --> 50:17.667
[Sighs]

50:17.700 --> 50:21.000
...because
it was too dangerous?

50:21.033 --> 50:24.200
What would
you have me do?

50:33.767 --> 50:35.333
[Radio whines]

50:35.367 --> 50:39.600
If you were paying me
to be your conscience, Marty,

50:39.633 --> 50:41.567
you should ask
for your money back.

50:43.233 --> 50:44.400
[Door opens]

50:44.433 --> 50:46.267
[Vehicle approaches]

50:51.667 --> 50:52.933
[Engine stops]

51:00.033 --> 51:01.300
[Light switch clicks]

51:01.333 --> 51:02.567
[Car door closes]

51:16.367 --> 51:18.600
[Car door opens]

51:22.800 --> 51:24.033
[Car door closes]

51:26.500 --> 51:27.900
[Car door opens]

51:31.300 --> 51:32.500
[Daniel grunts]

51:34.900 --> 51:36.933
[Daniel grunts]

51:49.100 --> 51:51.467
[Exhales softly]

51:51.500 --> 51:54.300
Becker:
He's waking up.

51:54.333 --> 51:56.300
**

51:56.333 --> 51:58.567
Litvak: Quick.

51:58.600 --> 52:01.567
**

52:01.600 --> 52:02.967
[Briefcase clatters]

52:03.000 --> 52:05.367
[Rattling]

52:05.400 --> 52:10.300
**

52:10.333 --> 52:11.633
[Syringe clicks]

52:11.667 --> 52:16.367
**

52:16.400 --> 52:18.467
[Groans softly]

52:18.500 --> 52:25.267
**

52:25.300 --> 52:27.433
[Sighs]

52:27.467 --> 52:31.600
Becker: Switch them.

52:31.633 --> 52:33.200
What?

52:33.233 --> 52:36.133
You said Anna was
a psychopath.

52:36.167 --> 52:38.400
If there's an accident,
having her behind the wheel

52:38.433 --> 52:41.300
will play
into their imaginations.

52:41.333 --> 52:44.000
Salim is
a steady driver.

52:44.033 --> 52:46.067
**

52:46.100 --> 52:47.467
[Door opens, hinges creak]

52:47.500 --> 52:49.933
[Keys rattle]

52:49.967 --> 52:51.100
[Door closes]

52:51.133 --> 52:52.400
[Keys rattle]

52:52.433 --> 52:53.667
[Light switch clicks]

52:53.700 --> 53:00.700
**

53:01.633 --> 53:08.600
**

53:09.467 --> 53:11.967
Michel: "You are mine,
and I'm yours, Charlie."

53:12.000 --> 53:14.600
[Seatbelts click]
"You are my soldier.

53:14.633 --> 53:17.400
Together, we will
put the match to the fuse.

53:17.433 --> 53:19.600
For us, there is no law

53:19.633 --> 53:22.500
except the law that is born
each day under fire."
[Engine starts]

53:22.533 --> 53:23.767
[Gear cranks]

53:23.800 --> 53:25.833
[Foot pedal creaks]

53:25.867 --> 53:27.567
We're moving out.

53:27.600 --> 53:28.767
Kurtz:
[Over radio] Good.

53:28.800 --> 53:30.967
**

53:31.000 --> 53:33.967
[Engine revs]

53:34.000 --> 53:35.667
[Car door closes]

53:35.700 --> 53:36.833
[Engine revs]

53:36.867 --> 53:38.733
[Tires screech]

53:38.767 --> 53:40.867
Acts of violence
cannot be criminal

53:40.900 --> 53:44.933
when they are carried out in
opposition to a criminal state.

53:44.967 --> 53:47.033
If the Israelis bomb
our villages

53:47.067 --> 53:48.233
with fighter jets,

53:48.267 --> 53:50.800
and we have not
a single plane,

53:50.833 --> 53:54.200
if they send tanks
when we have only our fists,

53:54.233 --> 53:57.333
when nobody cares,
what else can we do...

53:57.367 --> 53:58.767
but terror?

53:58.800 --> 54:03.367
For terror is theatre.

54:03.400 --> 54:09.233
And sometimes the world
has to be lifted up by its neck

54:09.267 --> 54:12.267
before it will listen
to justice.

54:13.200 --> 54:15.900
Terror.

54:15.933 --> 54:18.533
Did I say terror?

54:18.567 --> 54:20.500
For terror is...

54:20.533 --> 54:22.100
[Bang, glass shatters]
...theatre.

54:22.133 --> 54:25.933
[Metal creaking]

54:25.967 --> 54:29.633
[Metal screeches]

54:29.667 --> 54:30.600
[Explosion]

54:30.633 --> 54:32.400
[Tires screech]

54:32.433 --> 54:35.167
[Flames crackle]

54:35.200 --> 54:37.133
[Light switch clicks]

54:37.167 --> 54:39.967
"You remember what I said
about my father?"
[Sniffles]

54:40.000 --> 54:42.300
"In order to welcome
his Jewish visitors,

54:42.333 --> 54:44.367
he kept the coffee
in the village guest house

54:44.400 --> 54:47.133
hot for them
all hours of the day.

54:47.167 --> 54:49.767
But when the Zionists
finally came,

54:49.800 --> 54:51.467
they attacked.

54:51.500 --> 54:53.667
My grandfather
had to sell his horse

54:53.700 --> 54:56.567
to buy a gun
to protect his family.

54:56.600 --> 55:00.467
They shot him
with that very same gun."

55:00.500 --> 55:01.667
[Explosion]

55:01.700 --> 55:05.267
[Glass shatters, metal clangs]

55:05.300 --> 55:07.733
[Flames crackling]

55:11.167 --> 55:13.600
[Crackling continues]

55:19.600 --> 55:22.533
[Sighs softly]

55:26.367 --> 55:31.267
**

55:31.300 --> 55:34.267
[Door opens]

55:34.300 --> 55:35.467
[Door closes]

55:35.500 --> 55:37.467
[Flames crackling]

55:37.500 --> 55:44.500
**

55:47.100 --> 55:51.400
Michel: "I will always love you,
my Joan.

55:51.433 --> 55:57.500
For now, our bodies
and our bloods are mixed.

55:57.533 --> 56:04.500
**

56:06.033 --> 56:13.033
**

56:13.667 --> 56:20.667
**

56:21.333 --> 56:28.333
**

56:29.067 --> 56:36.033
**
